==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disruption
<hw>Dis*rup"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>disruptio</ets>, <ets>diruptio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or
rending asunder, or the state of being rent asunder or broken in pieces;
breach; rent; dilaceration; rupture; <as>as, the <ex>disruption</ex> of
rocks in an earthquake; <ex>disruption</ex> of a state.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disruptive</ent>⟦br⟧
